The U.S. and Mozambican militaries have begun a week of joint training
exercises in peacekeeping and humanitarian relief operations.

Mozambique's defense ministry said Wednesday the exercises in Moamba district,
in southern Mozambique, will include about 800 Mozambican and 700 U.S.
personnel.

The ministry said the training will include a simulation of a conflict zone to
practice the peacekeeping and relief activities.

